\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Convergence rate as a continuous function of $f_{\qopname  \relax m{max}}$ threshold. Each panel = one noise level. Vertical reference lines: Sella default ($f_{\qopname  \relax m{max}}{<}0.05$, dotted), our canonical ($f_{\qopname  \relax m{max}}{<}0.01$, dashed). GAD's curves are step-shaped (plateaus around the Euler-step granularity); Sella's are smoother (QN+trust-region tightens forces continuously).\relax }}{4}{figure.caption.9}\protected@file@percent }
